# Adobe Engineering Standards

Enterprise engineering governance for this team. Follow these directives on every change.

## Python / FastAPI / SQLModel

- All API endpoints must include OpenAPI-compatible docstrings with `summary` and `description` fields.
- All new SQLModel model fields require an accompanying Alembic migration — never modify DB schema without one.
- Python type hints are mandatory on all function signatures — no bare `dict`, `Any`, or untyped returns.
- Use `Optional[X]` not `X | None` for nullable fields (Python 3.10 compatibility).

## TypeScript / React

- All React components must use explicitly defined TypeScript interfaces for props — no inline type literals, no `any`.
- Component files must be co-located with their types in the same directory.
- All async functions must handle errors explicitly — no unhandled promise rejections.

## Accessibility (mandatory)

- All interactive elements must have an `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby` attribute.
- Colour-coded UI elements must include a non-colour indicator (icon, label, or pattern).
- Keyboard navigation must be supported for all interactive components.

## Testing

- Every new model field or API endpoint must have a corresponding test.
- Frontend component tests go in `__tests__/` adjacent to the component.

## General

- No `console.log` or `print` statements in committed code.
- All environment-specific config must come from environment variables, never hardcoded.
